        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 1:23PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 122 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jonesville, or near Hillsdale, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hillsdale, Jonesville, Litchfield, Jerome, Somerset, Pittsford,
Moscow, North Adams, Bear Lake, Allen, Lake Wilson, Shadyside, Osseo,
and Somerset Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
